Package org.csystem.util.datetime.legacy

Class DateTime

java.lang.Object
org.csystem.util.datetime.legacy.DateTime
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<DateTime>
@Deprecated(since="11.1.0", forRemoval=true) public final class DateTime extends Object implements Serializable, Comparable<DateTime>
Deprecated, for removal: This API element is subject to removal in a future version.
This class is not needed since Java 8. You can use Java 8 date time api instead of that class
That class is used for DateTime operations which simplifies Calendar and GregorianCalendar class
See Also:
